            <t:p>The Homily is attributed in
               <t:bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/VCHI8RJJ"><seg type="encyclopediaArticle"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Lusini2005EAEDersanaM"/><title level="a">Dǝrsanä Mikaʾel</title><title type="short">EAe</title><title level="m">Encyclopaedia Aethiopica</title><author><forename>Gianfrancesco</forename><surname>Lusini</surname></author><editor><forename>Siegbert</forename><surname>Uhlig</surname></editor><pubPlace>Wiesbaden</pubPlace><publisher>Harrassowitz Verlag</publisher><date>2005</date><biblScope unit="volume">II</biblScope><biblScope unit="page">139a-140a</biblScope><note type="tags"><note type="tag">bm:Lusini2005EAEDersanaM</note></note><note type="tag">bm:Lusini2005EAEDersanaM</note></t:bibl> 
               to <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10425Yohanne">Yoḥannǝs the Orthodox</t:persName>, but
               according to Denis Nosnitsin, it is attributed in most manuscripts to <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS8121RetuaH">Rǝtuʿa Hāymānot</t:persName>
               without mention of <t:persName ref="https://betamasaheft.eu/PRS10425Yohanne">Yoḥannǝs the Orthodox</t:persName>. It can be transmitted within <t:ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT1295Dersan">Dǝrsāna
                                                  Mikāʾel</t:ref> for Miyāzyā, sometimes (<t:ref type="mss" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/BAVet121">Vatican City, Biblioteca Apostolica Vaticana, Aeth. 121</t:ref>) for Tāḫśāś</t:p>
